spanGrp.span: Hegų hagoreižą hįkukuk hanįharegi nąąpak hogihira (ho)watekjanawi.
Once when I was young we went to pick cherries.
hegu haagoréiža hįįkukúk haniháregi nąąpák hogihíra wawatékjanawi
Heesge nąąnį eera nąąnį eerašąną (nįgiʔąp) no nįįʔąpnąkšąną eegi heesge eeja (ho)wataawi.
My mother, still living, said we would go there.
heske nąąníera nąąníerašana nįki'ąp no nį'ą́pnąkšana egi heske 'eeja wátaawi
nįgi'ąp = one of yours is living
Hira(w)ahasrašge cųųšgųnį nųnįge wąąk (wąąk) wažą_hokį waanįnįižą žeʔe hiira hicito haara hižą hirawahas gigi anąga ee howataawi.
We had no driver, one of our male relatives, one of our older brothers, we got him to drive.
hirá(w)ahas aške cųšgúni nųnį́ge wąąk wąąk wažóki wáanįnįža že'e híra hicitóhara hižą hirawáhas gigí áanaga e howatáwi
že'e hii-ra = wažą hii-ra 'the ones s/he is related to'
<<fs>Green> Green Bay sąikeja hahi eeja eeja Haramehi_hąąp nųųpahąxjį nįįsge eeja hahi haʔųwigųnį or taanįhą.
Past Green Bay we went for two or three Sundays.
Green Bay są́įgeja hahi 'eeja 'eeja harumíhe hąąp nųpahaxjį niské 'eeja hahi há'ųwįgųnį or tąąniha
doubled "Green" in the beginning -- LP: Ok, marked as false start.
Hąįnįgi xapgeįk hakika(w)aʔųwi anąga hegų mąįxeteižą mąąnąka ee hanį
We got up early in the morning, this white man who owned the land,
hąį́negi xap géį́g hakiká(w)a'ųwį áanaga hegu maíxeteižą mąąną́ka e hąnį
nąąpak hožu žeesge eeja peehi waaʔųwiną.
there we picked cherries (with a cherry bucket).
Hąįnįgi hąįnįxjįk hija haʔų reex hirarutiižą ruti hii anąga eeja reexra jagu gallon pail reexižą heesge hanąąc hižąšąną tuuswi anąga.
Early in the morning the wagon would come by and each of us would all take one of those pails.
hąį́egi hąínexjįg hijáų'ų reex hirarútiižą rutí hiaánaga 'eeja reéxra jagu gallon pail reéxižą heske hanaác hiašąna túzwi aánaga
Žee hoixjį hoixjį wahaawregi žige hiraruti hacįįja reexra watuswigi eeja haakja hanį hagiwi wąąkjeega hija wagaxšųnų.
When we filled them, we would take the pails back to the wagon that brought them and that man used to write it down.
žee hóixjį hóixjį wahą(w)į́negi žigé hirarúti hacį́ja reéxra watúzwigi 'eeja haákja hanįágį wąąk jega hijáwagaxšųnų
Jaanąga peehi raaš hija (h)įgitʼųp jaanąga peehi hija wagaxšųnų.
He put our name down and how many we picked he used to write down.
janą́ga péhi raažhij(ah)į́gįt'ųp janą́ga péhi hijáwagaxšųnų
Žeegų haawi anąga hakiijire waaʔųwį hegų.
žegu haí áanaga hakijíre wáa'ųwį hegu
Hąąpteʔe hegų nįge wažą heesge wažągašge mąąskook eeja woožu anąga nįgešge jaasge hįyaruwį anąga hąąke heesganį.
Today those things they are able to can or freeze them and that's the way we buy them, it wasn't that way.
že'e hą́pte'e gúnige wažą heske wažąkašge maáskokeja wožú áanaga nigéške jasgé hįyaruwį 'anąga ke heskánį
wažąkašge = that thing also (BO); *kašge hįwožuwi = we put them in (the tin cans) = we canned them ke hesgánį = isn't that right
something missing at 2:19? -- LP: Yes, but unclear.
Žeegu žuura kiikʼų nąąʔį waʔųajawi heesge (he)gų hakipanų haʔųwįšųnų.
We were trying to make money that's why we would race.
žégu žurá kik'ų ną́ą'i wá'ųąjawi héskegu hakipą́ną há'ųwįšųnų
One time I fell out of a tree.
Hanąąc mąija šiipre hąąke peehi tuuxuruknį.
They were all over the ground and I couldn't pick them all.
haną́ąc mąį́ja šípre ke pehí tuxúruknį
Nąąti haʔųwi anąga žeesge peehi waaʔųwišųnų.
We used to climb the trees and pick them.
nąątí ha'ų́wį áanaga žéske péhi wáa'ųwįšųnų
Hegų anąga eegi waakišipwira kuukjana(w)ira wareįka nąąnį eera žuura hiruwe gigi jaanąga reexra peehi hija ųanįha(w)i.
And then when we were finished and we were going to come back the white man payed my mother the money for all that we picked.
hegu áanaga egi wakíšipwira kukšana(w)íra wareį́ka nąąníera žurá hirawaígigi janága réxra péhi hija'uániha(w)i
Eeja anąga hige eeja guuwi eegi tookregi waaʔųaja(w)i hahi eeja cąąnįregi hige haʔųwi nąąnį eera hakaraikižu haʔų.
And then we came back, it was the summer time, and then in the fall I did it (again) along with my mother.
ejáanaga higeeja gúuwi egi tokrégi wa'ųąjá(w)i hahíeja cáanįnegi higé ha'ųwį nąąiera hakaraik hį'ųwį
hį'ųųwi doesn't make sense in there
Hicąk haara hakaraikižu nąąnį eera, eegi hoocąke peehiwi hacįįja wiigihiʔųra rušją anąga.
my younger sister and my mother, we would pick cranberries, wherever they finished raking.
hicąkhara karaík hį'ųwį nąąníera egi hocą́ke pehíwi hacį́ja wigíhi'ųną rušją́ąnaga
Eeja žee hoocąke hoocąke hirukąną haipį eeja hisge hapehi anąga,
There the cranberry boss, if we like to pick there,
'eeja že hocą́ke hiruką́na haipį́ eeja hiske hapéhi áanaga
We used to pick all the fallen ones.
Hegų bushel box heesge heesge eeja waažuwišųnų.
We used to put them in a bushel box.
hegu bušel box heske heskeja wáažuwišųnų
Hegų hoxjąnąregi tuušją(w)iregi hįyaha kookra hoixjį haawi hegų <<ui>> hegų hąąke kookra tuuʔą(w)inį hegų eeja nąk wahaa(w)i wareįka tuušjąiga wakurusšųnų hiruwe_hįgigiirawišųnų.
And then in the evening when we were finished if we filled a box we didn't carry the boxes, we left them there, in the evening the whiteman would come by and pick them up and they were paying us.
hegu hoxjaną́negi tušją́(w)įnegi hįyaha kokra hoixjihawi hegu ?? hegu ke kókra tu'ą́(w)įnį hegu eeja nąk'ųą́ha(w)i wareį́ka tušjąį́ga wakúrusšųnų higiru'éhįgigi ha'ųwįšųnų
higiru'éhįgigi ha'ųwįšųnų should be higiruwé hįgigirawįšųnų 'eeja nąk hii = he left it there
something missing at 4:49? -- LP: Yes, added <<ui>>
